{
  "stem": "11089.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So some people, the same-- the two sons, they survived with me-- the father.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Later on, they didn't come home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But at that time, they kept one here, one here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They dragged me into the camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they sent me to the first aid, it was called, [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Revere. ?] It was just a name for the world.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was nothing there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I came-- I went there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They gave me a number, D9.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "D9 means Dachau number 9, which means they have to wait for 200 people, then they take a transport and send them to Dachau to the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was number 9.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's when I was asking God, I want to die.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I can't take the pain.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I want to die.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So what again?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All of a sudden, they changed the doctor of the camp, a German.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the German doctor came every morning to check who was capable to go to work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he saw that, bodily, we are healthy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Only the bruises.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "If we would rest for a week or two in a warm place and had-- and have something, we can go back to work.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he didn't let us be sent to Dachau.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Before that-- Do you remember his name?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Before that, some people were sent already.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My best friends were-- went to Dachau already to be killed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I-- during those days, during those days, really, I got better.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I went back to work, but it didn't last long.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I fell sick, and they had to transfer me to a sick people's camp, to Lager IV, Kaufering.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I knew, here, that was the end, because here, you-- you didn't have to go to work.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
